ZH: 昨天我去看守所探望我的朋友。
EN: Yesterday, I visited my friend in the detention center.

ZH: 看守所限制家属探访时间。
EN: The detention center restricts visitation hours for family members.

ZH: 星期天在看守所是没有探访日。
EN: Sundays are not visiting days at the detention center.

ZH: 我们需要许可才能进入看守所。
EN: We need permission to enter the detention center.

ZH: 警察把罪犯带到了看守所。
EN: The police took the criminal to the detention center.

ZH: 看守所里的人员都受过专业培训。
EN: The staff at the detention center have all received professional training.

ZH: 在看守所里，罪犯必须遵守严格的规则。
EN: In the detention center, prisoners must adhere to strict rules.

ZH: 他已经在看守所待了一年了。
EN: He has been in the detention center for a year.

ZH: 看守所设有不同的区域用于不同类别的罪犯。
EN: The detention center has different sections for different categories of criminals.

ZH: 看守所提供基本的生活设施给囚犯。
EN: The detention center provides basic amenities for the inmates.

ZH: 我的律师正在为我申请保释出看守所。
EN: My lawyer is applying for my bail release from the detention center.

ZH: 他在看守所中度过了整个夏天。
EN: He spent the entire summer in the detention center.

ZH: 他在看守所里改过自新，现在生活已经重新开始了。
EN: He turned over a new leaf in the detention center and has now restarted his life.

ZH: 看守所周围设有高墙和警卫，确保安全。
EN: The detention center is surrounded by high walls and guards to ensure security.

ZH: 看守所的环境相对封闭，没有太多自由。
EN: The environment in the detention center is relatively confined with limited freedom.

ZH: 自从我出狱后，我决定不再回到看守所。
EN: Since I was released, I have decided never to return to the detention center.

ZH: 在看守所里，囚犯被监视并进行定期检查。
EN: In the detention center, inmates are monitored and undergo regular checks.

ZH: 看守所提供心理辅导给囚犯，帮助他们重建自信。
EN: The detention center provides psychological counseling to the inmates to help them rebuild their confidence.

ZH: 看守所里的囚犯被分配到不同的监房。
EN: Inmates in the detention center are assigned to different cells.

ZH: 看守所的管理人员负责维护秩序和安全。
EN: The management staff in the detention center are responsible for maintaining order and security.
